#compdef vaultwarden
# =============================================================================
# vaultwarden — Daniel García's "unofficial Bitwarden compatible
#                server written in Rust" (formerly known as
#                bitwarden_rs).  A self-hosted alternative to
#                the official Bitwarden Server with full API
#                compatibility — Bitwarden mobile/desktop/browser
#                clients connect to vaultwarden the same way they
#                connect to bitwarden.com.  Designed for users
#                who want to run a personal/family password
#                manager on their own hardware (Raspberry Pi,
#                home server, VPS, NAS, etc) without the
#                resource overhead of the official Bitwarden
#                Server (which requires .NET runtime + SQL Server
#                + Identity Server + multiple containers).
#                vaultwarden is a SINGLE Rust binary backed by
#                SQLite/MySQL/PostgreSQL — runs in <50MB RAM on
#                a Pi Zero.  Has become the de-facto self-
#                hosted password-manager server, with deployment
#                tutorials in every homelab blog and several
#                hundred Docker image variants.
#
# Author:  Daniel García (Spain) + 200+ contributors — Daniel
#          forked the original bitwarden_rs project in 2018 as a
#          personal Rust learning exercise; it grew into a
#          full-API-compatible alternative to Bitwarden Server.
#          Renamed from bitwarden_rs to vaultwarden in 2021 to
#          comply with Bitwarden trademark guidelines.
